# Date display format

- Show **date-only** values as `dd-mm-yyyy` (e.g. `12-07-2026`).
- Use [`frontend/src/utils/formatDate.js`](frontend/src/utils/formatDate.js) — `formatDate(value)` for display, `todayIsoDate()` for `<input type="date">` values.
- Keep `<input type="date">` / API wire values as ISO `yyyy-mm-dd` (or full ISO datetime from the API). Convert only at the display boundary.
- Do not display raw ISO date strings (`2026-07-12`) in UI labels, tables, or autocomplete options.
- Datetime-with-time (e.g. last login) may include time; still use day-first ordering (`dd-mm-yyyy`) for the date part when custom-formatting.
